In its efforts to lessen the hardship occasioned by the COVID-19 pandemic, Rachel the PIPER Foundation in collaboration with Mr Ekene Ezepue CEO FCT Alert News Magazine and her partners have donated relief materials to media organisations in Abuja. The foundation which is renowned for reaching out with acts of kindness before and during the covid-19 pandemic also carried out outreaches for IDP Camps and some communities in Kaduna State. Some of the media houses that benefitted from the gesture include NTA Network, NTA Sports, NAN and LEADERSHIP Newspapers with items such as face masks, food, hand sanitizers and mosquito nets. In a statement signed and made available to newsmen by the Founder, Amb (Chief) Rachel Bakam MABS, the Foundation said it will embark on the next outreach in Ungwan Gwari— Kawo Kaduna. Bakam appreciated partners including Mr Alex Nwankwo, CEO Amity Global Network, Comrade (Chief) Isaac Balami President Nigeria Rebirth Foundation and 7 Star Global Hangar, Mrs Diana Patrick President Gadnite and child aged Foundation, Mr E. R Offor who is supporting with cash among others. The Foundation which has won multiple award including Television Producer and Presenter, peace, tourism and anti human trafficking Ambassador is aiming to assist and support the emancipation and development of the less privilege people in the society. 